## Next Steps for Production Deployment

To complete the Speed Insights setup and start collecting metrics:

1. **Enable Speed Insights in Vercel Dashboard**
   - Navigate to your project in the Vercel dashboard
   - Go to the "Speed Insights" tab
   - Click "Enable" to activate the feature
   - This will add routes at `/_vercel/speed-insights/*` after deployment

2. **Deploy to Vercel**
   ```bash
   vercel deploy
   ```
   Or connect your Git repository for automatic deployments

3. **Verify Installation**
   - After deployment, inspect the page source
   - Confirm the presence of `/_vercel/speed-insights/script.js` in the `<body>` tag
   - This script is automatically injected by the `<SpeedInsights />` component

4. **View Metrics**
   - After real users visit the site, metrics will appear in the Speed Insights dashboard
   - Data typically appears within a few hours of deployment
   - Full insights available after a few days of visitor traffic

## Implementation Notes

- The implementation follows the official Vercel Speed Insights documentation for React applications
- The `<SpeedInsights />` component is placed at the app root level for comprehensive tracking
- No additional configuration is required - the component works out of the box
- The integration is production-ready and will start collecting metrics upon deployment to Vercel

